comments: Theis (BOS) sets the screen on Holiday (MIL) and absorbs the contact.
Holiday (MIL) and Theis (BOS) engage and disengage with one another after Theis begins rolling toward the lane.
Connaughton (MIL) firms up in his screening position in Smart's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact by collapsing his arms. Smart's reaction is not consistent with the amount of contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) goes to, not through, Theis' (BOS) space and spins off of the contact made inside the lane.
As Theis (BOS) falls to the floor, he makes marginal contact with Antetokounmpo (MIL).
Middleton's (MIL) arm is extended slightly forward and marginal contact occurs with Brown's (BOS) left arm as he makes the pass.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is in the lane for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Connaughton (MIL) legally contests the shot attempt by Tatum (BOS).
Brown (BOS) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) engage and disengage with one another following the pick.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) places his left arm against Tatum (BOS) during his driving shot attempt but the contact is marginal.
Teague (BOS) makes contact with the ball and the part of DiVincenzo's (MIL) hand that is on the ball during the driving shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) briefly has his arms around Theis' (BOS) upper half before correcting.
Theis (BOS) makes marginal contact with Middleton (MIL) during the screen.
Theis (BOS) firms up in his screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in Brown's (BOS) path and does not deliver the contact.
Theis (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and does not deliver the contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) extends into Brown's (BOS) path as Brown attempts to avoid the contact.
Theis (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and does not deliver the contact.
Theis (BOS) steps into the lane before Antetokounmpo (MIL) releases the free throw.

Thompson (BOS) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) both make a legal attempt to reach the inbound pass, and the contact should have been deemed incidental.  Referees reviewed the call in instant replay as per the automatic trigger for fouls called at when there is no time remaining on the clock at the end of any period to confirm that the foul was called before the expiration of time, but the foul itself is not a reviewable matter.
Johnson (PHX) makes contact to Doncic's (DAL) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Kleber's (DAL) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact.
Richardson (DAL) makes contact to Booker's (PHX) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Kleber (DAL) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Paul (PHX) after the ball is released during his jump shot attempt.
Doncic (DAL) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a legal position in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact during the pick.
Kleber (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position during Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Kleber (DAL) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).
Robinson (MIA) places a collapsed arm to Fournier's (ORL) side defending his drive to the basket.
Robinson (MIA) jumps vertically when he defends Fultz's (ORL) play at the basket.
Vucevic (ORL) reaches in and makes marginal contact with Dragic (MIA) that does not affect his SQBR.
Fournier (ORL) makes contact to Adebayo's (MIA) body during his shooting motion that affects his shot attempt.
Dragic (MIA) makes contact with Fultz's (ORL) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Gordon (ORL) places an arm to Dragic's (MIA) front during his drive to the basket and the contact is marginal.
Butler (MIA) establishes legal screening position in Fultz's (ORL) path during the pick and does not deliver contact.
Dragic (MIA) moves laterally towards Fultz (ORL), who spins away from contact and does not dislodge Dragic from his defensive position.
Iguodala (MIA) engages with Vucevic (ORL) off ball and does not affect his ability to get to the pass.
Iguodala (MIA) makes contact to Fournier's (ORL) body that affects his play at the basket.
Vucevic (ORl) legally contests Dragic's (MIA) driving shot attempt.
Dragic (MIA) makes marginal contact with Fultz (ORL) when he reaches in.
Adebayo (MIA) makes marginal contact with Fultz (ORL) as he makes the pass.
Iguodala (MIA) moves into Ross' (ORL) space and makes body contact that affects his SQBR.
Adebayo (MIA) and Gordon (ORL) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Herro (MIA) commits a take foul on Gordon (ORL).
Adebayo (MIA) establishes legal position in Fultz's (ORL) path during the pick and absorbs the contact.
Vucevic (ORL) makes marginal contact with Dragic (MIA) as he drives to the basket.
Dragic (MIA) commits a take foul on Fournier (ORL).
Simmons (PHI) splits his feet on the perimeter.
At the end of the drive, Embiid (PHI) loses control of his dribble on the spin move and Westbrook (WAS) makes marginal contact to Embiid's off-ball hand.
Embiid (PHI) loses control of the ball and does not restart his dribble as he attempts to regain control.
Bryant (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Curry (PHI).
Bryant (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Milton's (PHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
As Beal (WAS) starts his dribble, Milton (PHI) has a legal resting hand on Beal (WAS) that he neither extends nor delivers contact with.
Embiid (PHI) makes contact to Bryant's (WAS) arm that affects his play at the basket.
Bonga (WAS) does not extend his arm or deliver contact to Simmons' (PHI) back during the rebound.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Beal's (WAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bryant (WAS) makes marginal contact with Embiid's (PHI) arm that does not affect his play at the basket.
Beal (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Harris' (PHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Milton (PHI) immediately slides his hand off Bryant's (WAS) waist as he engages on the screen and the contact does not affect Bryant's FOM.
Bonga (WAS) makes clean ball contact to knock it away from Harris (PHI) during the rebound attempt.
Harris (PHI) cleanly dislodges the ball away from Bryant (WAS) during the rebound.
Bonga (WAS) makes contact to Milton's (PHI) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Bryant (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Milton's (PHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Beal's (WAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bryant (WAS) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Simmons' (PHI) arm and body that affects his play at the basket.
Bryant (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Thybulle's (PHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Milton (PHI) and Westbrook (WAS) engage and disengage during the inbound.
Westbrook (WAS) commits a take foul on Harris (PHI).
Prior to Beal (WAS) receiving the pass, Thybulle (PHI) reaches around the screen to make contact with Beal that affects his FOM.
Bryant (WAS) commits a take foul on Curry (PHI).
Bryant (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Simmons' (PHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Prior to the pass, Simmons (PHI) makes clean ball contact as he tries to dislodge the ball from Beal (WAS).
Jackson (DET) releases from contact with Beasley (MIN) during his drive to the basket.
Towns (MIN) makes marginal contact with Jackson (DET) during his pass underneath the basket.
Plumlee (DET) makes marginal contact with Towns (MIN) defending his drive to the basket.
Towns (MIN) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Jackson (DET) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Plumlee (DET) and Okogie (MIN) engage and disengage while rebounding.
Rubio (MIN) establishes legal position in Plumlee's (DET) path during the screen and absorbs contact.
Towns (MIN) draws Plumlee (DET) into the air towards him and the contact results in a foul on Plumlee (DET) even if contact is initiated by Towns (MIN).
Rubio (MIN) makes incidental contact to Griffin's (DET) arm after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Plumlee (DET) makes marinal contact with Russell (MIN) after he passes the ball.
Jackson (DET) makes contact to Okogie's (MIN) arm that affects his play at the basket.
During his jump shot attempt, Grant (DET) initiates contact with Rubio (MIN), who is in a legal guarding position.
A 24 second violation is correctly called.
Barnes (SAC) splits his pivot foot prior to the start of his drive.
Jokic (DEN) makes contact to the body of Barnes (SAC) during his shooting motion that disrupts his driving shot attempt.

Replay review of the foul called on Murray (DEN) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Murray cups Whiteside's (SAC) side, who is making a legal attempt to block the shot, and there is no clear and conclusive evidence to overturn the call on the floor.
Millsap (DEN) makes contact to the arm of Whiteside (SAC) during his shooting motion that disrupts his play at the basket.
Hield (SAC) wraps the upper body of Jokic (DEN) while trying to defend around the screen being set.
Harris (DEN) makes marginal two hand contact to Fox's (SAC) body as he receives the inbound pass.
Jokic (DEN) uses both hands and pushes Joseph (SAC) while setting the pick. Disrupting his ability to defend.
Whiteside (SAC) makes contact to Jokic's (DEN) wrist/arm that causes him to lose possession of the ball.
Whiteside (SAC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Barton (DEN) firms up and absorbs the contact.
Porter Jr. (DEN) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Fox (SAC) after the release that does not affect his shot attempt.
Hield (SAC) makes marginal contact to Porter Jr's (DEN) body during his layup attempt, and does not disrupts his shooting motion.
Whiteside (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Jokic (DEN).
Barton (DEN) makes marginal contact to Barnes' (SAC) body as he gathers and enters his shooting motion.
Whiteside (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position as Barton (DEN) initiates the contact during his driving shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) grabs the rim when the ball is outside of the cylinder.
Fox (SAC) makes marginal contact with Barton (DEN) when he makes the pass.
Joseph (SAC) commits a take foul on Harris (DEN).
Fox (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Barton (DEN) and cleanly blocks the dunk.
Barnes (SAC) takes more than two steps after gathering the ball.
Barnes (SAC) makes contact to Jokic's (DEN) arms as he receives the inbound pass and causes him to lose possession of the ball.
Barton (DEN) jumps from point A to point B into Barnes (SAC) and makes contact with his arm and body that affect the dunk attempt.
